Title: Order sentences based on similarity
Description: Read the paragraph and order the sentences below it. On top the most similar and at the bottom the less similar.
RequesterFeedback: We noticed you need to more carefully read the paragraph and the sentences.
Input.leadParagraph: For most types of cancer, doctors use staging information to help plan treatment and to predict a person's outlook (prognosis). Although each person's situation is different, cancers with the same stage tend to have similar outlooks and are often treated the same way. The cancer stage is also a way for doctors to describe the extent of the cancer when they talk with each other about a person's cancer.
Input.similarParagraph_1: Even though not all new lumps or masses are malignant, they should be checked by a doctor to determine its risks.
Input.similarParagraph_2: Before taking herbal products, that may help some deal with cancer side effects, patients should consult with their doctor.
Input.similarParagraph_3: The advancement of cancer is categorized and described in stages, which also works as a guide for treatment and prediction.
Input.similarParagraph_4: Doctors usually use stages for cancer so they can predict the evolution and can choose the treatment. Actually they can describe the extension of the tumor through staging.
Input.similarParagraph_5: When doctors are dealing with cancer patients, Oncologists use staging information as a reference to determine the severity of the patient, and their treatment as well.  Even though each patient has their own characteristics, there are similar symptoms during each disease's stage.
Input.similarParagraph_6: Each person with cancer is unique, but cancer stages allow doctors to group similar patients together when they discuss treatment options and outcomes.

Input.similarParagraph_5: When doctors are dealing with cancer patients, Oncologists use staging information as a reference to determine the severity of the patient, and their treatment as well.  Even though each patient has their own characteristics, there are similar symptoms during each disease's stage.
Input.similarParagraph_6: Each person with cancer is unique, but cancer stages allow doctors to group similar patients together when they discuss treatment options and outcomes.
